I‘m not the biggest fan of store bought baked beans but I absolutely love making my own 🥰

The recipe Alex and I normally use takes a bit longer than the one I used today but if you have a bit of time on your hands it’s the perfect bean recipe 🤩

This one on the other hand is incredibly quick! All you need is
🍅 200g passata
🍅 1 tin of cannellini beans
🍅 smoked paprika
🍅 chilli powder
🍅 Salt and Pepper

And all you need to do is fry the onion, add your spices, add the passata and let it simmer for about 5 minutes. Once the 5 minutes are over add the beans and let it simmer again for 5 minutes. It’s super quick and easy 🤩

I had the beans on some sourdough which was rubbed with fresh garlic und put under the grill. Super easy but so delicious 🤩

